                    "description": "Since graduating as MSc in Experimental Physics in 1984, I have worked in Technology / ICT related roles, starting as a Software Engineer and Project Leader and continuing in (project) management, consulting and executive (CIO / CTO / Director IT / CEO) roles. \n\nAfter 10 years in Professional roles, I became CIO for Aon Holdings in 1994, responsible for Europe, Middle East, Africa, Asia and Australia. \n\nIn 2000, I became an independent contractor. Assignments were focused on (digital) transformation and (business) improvement and include CIO, ICT Executive, Program Management and General Management positions at Van Oord, Ahold ECommerce, SNS REAAL, UWV, TMG, Goudse Verzekeringen, University of Amsterdam, Hogeschool van Amsterdam, PWN and Nuon. Several consulting assignments completed for Startup Companies, Waterschappen, Curam, IBM and ProRail. \n\nDuring my 33+ year career, I have worked for 25+ organizations in the public and private sector, both on interim assignments and as an employee. Main roles are CIO / Director IT (16 years / 8 organizations), Line Management (5 years / 4 organizations), Program Management (3 years / 2 organizations), Advise (3 years / 8 organizations) and IT Professional (6 years / 3 organizations).\n\nI have been responsible for organizations up to 1.400 people, annual budgets up to Euro 400 million and outsourcing contracts up to Euro 400 million. \n\nPlease see below for further details on roles and responsibilities.",
